2650	\begin{proof}
2651	  \uses{lem:injective_of_adjoint}
2652	  For injective \(I\), injectivity gives that \(\operatorname{Hom}(-, I)\) carries
2653	  epimorphisms to epimorphisms. Combined with the automatic preservation of finite limits
2654	  (left exactness), the short-exact-sequence criterion shows it preserves finite colimits;
2655	  hence, being also left exact, it preserves homology. A functor that preserves homology
2656	  sends quasi-isomorphisms of chain complexes to quasi-isomorphisms degreewise, which is
2657	  the second statement.
2658	\end{proof}
